The `Test-OpenCodeProviders.ps1` script validates that all configured OpenCode AI providers are working correctly by automatically testing connectivity to each one. It discovers your configured providers, selects a test model from each, sends a simple message, and checks for a successful response. This helps OpenCode users identify which providers are functioning and which have issues like authentication problems, unsupported models, or service outages. Results are displayed in a clear table showing each provider's status, response time, and any errors. This automated testing saves users from manually testing each provider and ensures they can quickly identify which providers are ready for use in their AI workflows.
